          "title": "Service settings",
          "helpText": {
            "aws": "Note, you are charged standard request, storage, and data transfer rates to read to and write from AWS services, such as Amazon S3, Amazon EFS, Amazon FSx, and AWS Key Management Service (KMS). When copying data from AWS to storage on premises or in other clouds, you pay AWS Data Transfer OUT charges from your source AWS Region. When copying data between AWS Regions, you pay for Data Transfer between Regions. When copying data between AWS services using the AWS DataSync EC2 agent, you pay for Data Transfer between Regions and for Data Transfer between Availability Zones. You are also charged standard rates for Amazon CloudWatch Logs, Amazon CloudWatch Events, and Amazon CloudWatch Metrics. You will be billed by AWS PrivateLink for interface VPC endpoints that you create to manage and control the traffic between your agent(s) and the DataSync service over AWS PrivateLink.",
            "aws-cn": "Note, you are charged standard request, storage, and data transfer rates to read to and write from Amazon services, such as Amazon S3, Amazon EFS, Amazon FSx, and Amazon Key Management Service (KMS). When copying data from Amazon to storage on premises or in other clouds, you pay AMazon Data Transfer OUT charges from your source Amazon Region. When copying data between Amazon Regions, you pay for Data Transfer between Regions. When copying data between Amazon services using the Amazon DataSync EC2 agent, you pay for Data Transfer between Regions and for Data Transfer between Availability Zones. You are also charged standard rates for Amazon CloudWatch Logs, Amazon CloudWatch Events, and Amazon CloudWatch Metrics. You will be billed by Amazon PrivateLink for interface VPC endpoints that you create to manage and control the traffic between your agent(s) and the DataSync service over Amazon PrivateLink."
          },
          "helpUrl": {
            "$LINK": {
              "type": "pricing",
              "path": "/datasync/pricing/"
            }
          },
          "bodyText": {
            "aws": "AWS DataSync offers simple, predictable, pay-as-you-go pricing. You pay a flat, per-gigabyte fee for the amount of data transferred between your storage locations. Tasks configured for Enhanced mode are also charged a fee per task execution. Additional storage, request, transfer, logging, and monitoring fees for other AWS Services still apply. See the information sidebar on the right for more detail.",
            "aws-cn": "Amazon DataSync has predictable, usage-based pricing. With DataSync you pay for the amount of data that you copy. Additional storage, request, transfer, logging and monitoring fees for other services still apply. See the information sidebar on the right for more detail."
          },
